# Side Router Deploy

Use this rule when working on Ubuntu side-router deployment, review, or outage diagnosis.

## Safety

- Treat gateway, DNS, iptables, TProxy, and service restart changes as high risk.
- Prefer planning mode unless the user explicitly asks for direct execution and provides login access.
- Always produce rollback steps for risky changes.
- If the user reports no internet, guide temporary gateway and DNS recovery first.

